2 cups all-purpose flour
2 teaspoons baking soda
1 teaspoon balsamic vinegar
3 tablespoons almond butter
2 eggs
1/4 teaspoon salt
1 cup mashed ripe bananas

Instructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Coat loaf pan with nonstick spray.

2. In a bowl, stir together sugar, flour, baking powder, and baking soda.

3. Make well in center of flour mixture; set aside.

4. Stir together cooled coffee, vinegar, almond butter, eggs, and salt.

5. Add banana mashed into bottom of pan.

6. Carefully stir in flour mixture until just moist.

7. Pour batter into loaf pan.

8. Bake until top is golden brown and toothpick inserted into center of bread comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes.

9. Let cool in pan 10 minutes. Transfer bread to rack to cool completely.
